<p>A boat carrying migrants sank off the Tunisian coast on Wednesday, leaving at least 40 people dead — including infants — and dozens rescued, local judicial authorities said [bbc.com#1][allafrica.com#1][thehindu.com#1]. Officials say those on board were from sub‑Saharan African countries and that around 30 people were pulled alive from the water and taken to safety [bbc.com#1][japantoday.com#1][newarab.com#1]. The sinking is one more deadly example of the risks faced by people using the central Mediterranean route to try to reach Europe [bbc.com#1][newarab.com#1].</p><h3>Highlights:</h3><ul><li>Initial probe: A Mahdia public prosecutor&#x27;s office spokesman, Walid Chtabri, said initial investigations put the number on board at about 70 and confirmed recovery of 40 bodies while others were rescued [newarab.com#1].</li><li>Geographic context: Tunisia&#x27;s coast lies about 145 kilometres from the Italian island of Lampedusa, making it a frequent departure point for migrants attempting the central Mediterranean crossing [newarab.com#1].</li><li>Route danger: The International Organization for Migration (IOM) estimates the central Mediterranean route has seen 32,803 people dead or missing since 2014, illustrating the route&#x27;s high lethality [newarab.com#1].</li><li>Policy background: Tunisia signed a €255 million deal with the European Union in 2023 — nearly half the package was intended to address irregular migration — a context that has affected controls and returns policies [newarab.com#1].</li><li>Recent migration flows: UN refugee agency figures cited in reporting show more than 55,000 irregular migrants have arrived in Italy so far this year, with nearly 4,000 departures estimated from Tunisia [newarab.com#1].</li></ul><blockquote>Initial investigations indicate that there were 70 people on board the vessel. - Walid Chtabri</blockquote><h3>Perspectives:</h3><ul><li>Mahdia public prosecutor&#x27;s office (spokesman Walid Chtabri): Initial investigations indicate there were around 70 people on board; 40 bodies were recovered and 30 people were rescued, according to the office&#x27;s spokesman. (<a href='https://www.newarab.com/news/40-african-migrants-dead-shipwreck-tunisia'>The New Arab</a>)</li><li>UN Refugee Agency (UNHCR): Over 55,000 irregular migrants have arrived in Italy so far this year, with the majority departing from Libya and nearly 4,000 from Tunisia, highlighting persistent cross‑Mediterranean flows. (<a href='https://www.newarab.com/news/40-african-migrants-dead-shipwreck-tunisia'>The New Arab</a>)</li><li>Tunisian authorities (general): Local judicial authorities have reported the casualties and are overseeing the recovery and investigation on the ground. (<a href='https://www.thehindu.com/news/international/at-least-40-migrants-including-infants-die-in-boat-sinking-off-tunisia/article70191444.ece'>The Hindu</a>)</li></ul><h3>Sources:</h3><ul><li><a href='https://allafrica.com/stories/202510230200.html'>Africa: At Least 40 African Migrants Die As Boat Sinks Off Tunisia</a> - allafrica.com</li><li><a href='https://www.bbc.com/news/articles/c0rp5805ykzo'>Forty migrants, including infants, die as boat sinks off Tunisia</a> - bbc.com</li><li><a href='https://japantoday.com/category/world/40-migrants-including-infants-die-in-boat-sinking-off-tunisia'>40 migrants, including infants, die in boat sinking off Tunisia</a> - japantoday.com</li><li><a href='https://www.thehindu.com/news/international/at-least-40-migrants-including-infants-die-in-boat-sinking-off-tunisia/article70191444.ece'>At least 40 migrants, including infants, die in boat sinking off Tunisia</a> - thehindu.com</li><li><a href='https://www.newarab.com/news/40-african-migrants-dead-shipwreck-tunisia'>40 African migrants dead in shipwreck off Tunisia</a> - newarab.com</li></ul>